##
# cc_allow
#
# Country Code allow list — permit traffic only from countries listed here,
# blocking all other countries. This inverts the default: if cc_allow.rules
# has entries, all countries NOT listed are blocked.
#
# When both cc_deny.rules and cc_allow.rules have entries, deny takes
# precedence (deny is evaluated first in the chain order).
#
# Requires ipset (USE_IPSET="auto" or "1") for high-performance matching.
#
# Format: one entry per line, blank lines and lines starting with # are ignored.
#
# Simple syntax — allow all traffic from/to a country:
#   US
#   CA
#   GB
#
# Continent shorthand — expands to all countries in the continent:
#   @NA
#   @EU
#
# Supported continents: @AF (Africa), @AS (Asia), @EU (Europe),
# @NA (North America), @SA (South America), @OC (Oceania)
#
# Advanced syntax — allow specific protocol/port/direction per country:
#   proto:flow:[s/d]=port:[s/d]=CC
#
# Examples:
#   Allow inbound SSH only from US:     tcp:in:d=22:s=US
#   Allow inbound HTTP from EU:         tcp:in:d=80:s=@EU
#
# Temporary entries use the same ttl=/expire= syntax as allow/deny_hosts.rules.
#
##
